# Sector Rotation Backtest Strategy

A Python-based backtesting framework comparing four portfolio allocation 
strategies using sector ETF data, Fama-French factors, and MACD-based 
regime filtering.

---

##Architecture

Kenneth French Data Library --> Python (pandas, numpy) --> Strategy Backtesting --> Performance Analysis

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer              | Tool                        |
|--------------------|-----------------------------|
| Data Source        | Kenneth French Data Library |
| Data Processing    | Python (pandas, numpy)      |
| Visualization      | matplotlib, seaborn         |
| Environment        | Jupyter Notebook            |

---

## Strategies Compared

1. **Equal Weighted** — equal allocation across all 49 industries monthly
2. **Inverse Volatility** — weights inversely proportional to 12-month rolling volatility
3. **Relative Strength (RS)** — long improving sectors, short weakening sectors using RS Ratio and RS Momentum
4. **RS Dynamic** — switches between RS strategy and Inverse Volatility based on MACD market signal

---

## Key Results

| Strategy           | CAGR (%) | Sharpe Ratio |
|--------------------|----------|--------------|
| Equal Weighted     | 10.94    | 0.452        |
| Inverse Volatility | 10.89    | 0.467        |
| Relative Strength  | 13.30    | 0.486        |
| RS Dynamic         | 12.32    | 0.475        |

The Relative Strength strategy outperformed the passive benchmarks by 
over 20% in CAGR while maintaining the highest Sharpe ratio.

